---<br>
<br>
My method was real simple. First i cast a bunch of monster summoning 2 pets till i couldnt anymore, and remembered what fragment % of mana i had left over. This would help establish a rough estimate of mana cost per pet, which i will need to figure out total mana gain per pet.<br>
<br>
Then i did another test, this time i started from low mana %, and reclaimed till fm. This would help tell me how much profit mana i gained per sec, per tic, and per pet while doing pet canni.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Stats</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: I am a L64 magician with a total mana pool of 4253. i have spell casting mastery 3, a summoning efficiency 3 item (up to 25% savings per cast on pets), and a total standing mana regen of 21 for this test (note to self: get a summoning efficiency 3+ item which does not take a flowing thought spot).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Test 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: casting pets till oom. Starting from 100% mana, i was able to cast 44 pets till i stopped at about 6% mana. This took 8 minutes and 27 seconds.<br>
<br>
Basically, to find the mana each pet cost, what i need to do is subtract the mana left over after casting from your total mana pool, add mana gained from your mana regen value during the course of the test, and divide that by the number of times you could cast the spell.<br>
I found that out using this formula.<br>
4253 - 6(4253 * .01) + 21(507/6) / 44 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>131.2 mana cost per pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
So, now we know pets cost a mage with scm3, summoning efficiency item, and spec conjuration about 131.2 mana each.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Test 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: reclaiming pets till fm. I started with 18% mana, and it took me 15 pets and roughly 2 mins and 48 seconds to reach fm.<br>
<br>
I do something similar with the last test only this time i subtract the total regenned mana from relevent resources rather than add it. I then divided that by the time in seconds elapsed for the test, which tells me how much mana/second i am generating from pet canni. I divide that number by 6 to tell me mana per tic. I divide the original number by number of pets i could cast to tell me profit mana per reclaim, and then i add that to mana cost per pet to tell me net mana gain per reclaim.<br>
<br>
4253 - 18(4253 * .01) - 21(168/6) / 168 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>17.26 profit mana gain per sec</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
17.26 * 6 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>103.55 profit mana gain per tic</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
4253 - 18(4253 * .01) - 21(168/6) / 15 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>193.3 profit mana gain per reclaim</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
193.3 + 131.2 = <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>324.5 total mana gain per reclaim</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
193.3 mana is 4-5% of my total mana pool regenerated per reclaim, which sounds right from what i observed visually. This will be more if your mana pool is smaller, or less if its larger.<br>
<br>
So basically, if you have a summoning efficiency item, conjuration spec, and spell casting mastery 3, using pet canni results in a mana gain of roughly 193.3 per cast, and a mana regen while actively canniblizing of 17.26 per second, or 103.55 per tic. If you use jboots to bypass the refresh delay (i did not) this number can rise even more.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Pet reclaim in action</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
My dr sucks, so a pet is kinda risky on cursed, therefore i do not use one. However this doesnt effect my performance all that badly, since with a gift of xev full of malachite i can regen mana quite fast to increase nuking dps.<br>
<br>
I logged the last cursed fight i participated in. It lasted 22 minutes and 3 seconds (or just 1323 seconds). During this time i was able to deal 100,021 damage to cursed resulting in a nuking dps of 75.6. This could have been higher, but people kept whining for mod rods and arrows and things. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I reclaimed for mana 24 ms2 pets during this time. At about 193 mana gain per pet, that results in  4,632 extra mana, 3.5 mana per second, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>21 mana per tic</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> over the course of 22 minutes we fought him!<br>
<br>
Out of 46 effective blasts on cursed, my average hit was 2176 (spell casting fury 2). From earlier tests, i know that for a conjuration specced mage with spell casting mastery 3 using the bauble, this spell costs roughly 409 mana. Thats a ratio of 5.32. So, a mana regen gain of 21 mana/tic results in a dps gain of 18.62.<br>
<br>
While it isnt quite the 50ish dps from servant of marr, pet canni used liberally will result in a dps boost upward of 19 on cursed for a mage with the proper aa/focus item.<br>
<br>
Things to know:<br>
*Mana preservation <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>is not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as good as summoning efficiency. Mana preservation is up to a 10% savings, summoning efficiency is up to 25%. Get yourself an enshrouded veil or other summoning efficiency 3+ item to work with.<br>
*<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do not buy improved reclaim energy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, it is a stealth nerf to this technique. It changes the formula and makes reclaiming less profitable.<br>
*The sol ro focus items work well for instant reclaim, hot key them and your gtg.<br>
*Jboots may be used to bypass the refresh delay increasing the speed at which you cannibilize.<br>
